I now have a complete picture of all the code reuse issues. Let me compile the findings.

Here is the review of the `feat/mail` branch changes, focused exclusively on code reuse issues.

---

## Reviewing: feat/mail branch (8 files)

---

## Critical Issues

None - no newly written code that directly duplicates an existing utility with an identical signature that is simply not called.

---

## Important Issues

### Issue 1: Duplicated sender-lookup logic across three call sites (confidence: 95)

**Files and lines:**
- `/home/openclaw/code/tuicraft/src/ui/tui.ts` lines 216-219 (`mail-read` case)
- `/home/openclaw/code/tuicraft/src/daemon/commands.ts` lines 657-660 (`mail_read` case)
- `/home/openclaw/code/tuicraft/src/daemon/commands.ts` lines 681-684 (`mail_read_json` case)

All three sites contain identical logic to resolve the sender name for a player mail:

```typescript
let sender = "Unknown";
if (entry.senderGuid !== undefined) {
  const guidLow = Number(entry.senderGuid & 0xffffffffn);
  sender = handle.getNameCache().get(guidLow) ?? "Unknown";
}
